	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65334315"><p>Part of it is because Unicode is broken and doesn't provide adequate support to developers. Part of it is because major operating systems like Windows are case insensitive and developers are really looking for how best to support NTFS and FAT, not how to avoid security issues on Linux.</p><p>Replacing Unicode would do a lot to help with this. Most of the rest is down to less than ideal operating system design.</p></div>
	</div>

